<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Hyperbolic_cosine">Hyperbol=
ic cosine</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-=
bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHy=
perbolic_functions&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Edit section=
: Hyperbolic cosine"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bra=
cket">]</span></span></div>
<p>It can be shown that the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Area_u=
nder_the_curve" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Area under the curve">area u=
nder the curve</a> of the hyperbolic cosine (over a finite interval) is alw=
ays equal to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arc_length" title=
=3D"Arc length">arc length</a> corresponding to that interval:<sup id=3D"ci=
